The Export Promotion Industrial Park, also known as EPIP, is a multiple-product export processing zone in Bihar and East India developed by the Ministry of Commerce and Industry, the Government of Bihar and by the administrative body BIADA located in Hajipur, the zonal headquarter of the East Central Railway Zone. The Export Promotion Industrial Park of Hajipur, in the administrative Vaishali district, has 94 acres (38 ha; 0.147 sq mi) of land with modern infrastructure.
